<subSubSection id="C37165043C6E2E4D42E5FB0CFC92B5A5" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BD4368F3C6E2E4D42E5FB0CFCC4B57D" blockId="10.[151,1437,1257,2039]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">
<emphasis id="B91FEA9D3C6E2E4D42E5FB0CFF31B615" bold="true" box="[151,214,1257,1283]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Type.</emphasis>
In the original description, Suffrian did not mention the number of the studied specimens but he reported the name of single collector (Sellow), a single locality (“Allegrette”) and a single type location (
<collectionCode id="ED7AAE4A3C6E2E4D46CDFAE8FACAB631" box="[1215,1325,1293,1319]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">MNHUB</collectionCode>
), where a single 
<typeStatus id="54D0882D3C6E2E4D4293FAD4FEDFB65D" box="[225,312,1329,1355]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">syntype</typeStatus>
has been tracked down. As the MNHUB catalogue quotes a single specimen forming the type series, this one must be considered the 
<typeStatus id="54D0882D3C6E2E4D438FFAB0FDB8B679" box="[509,607,1365,1391]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">holotype</typeStatus>
by monotypy (ICZN, Art. 72.4.1.1 and Art. 73.1.2). The label information of the specimen matches the registration data from the old catalogue of the MNHUB (“23960 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D0C3C6E2E4D46C3FA9CFF3EB6A1" authority="Suffr." authorityName="Suffrian" authorityYear="1866" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Metallactus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albivittis">Metallactus albivittis Suffr.</taxonomicName>
* 1. Allegrette, Sello”). The typification has been made as follows, in order to stabilize the epithet. 
<typeStatus id="54D0882D3C6E2E4D4755FA78FA73B6A3" box="[1319,1428,1437,1463]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">HOLOTYPE</typeStatus>
: 
<specimenCount id="9D6DFD063C6E2E4D42E5FA24FF49B6CD" box="[151,174,1473,1499]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
, glued, aedeagus glued on the same card bearing the specimen, abdomen glued on a separate card // “23960” [white label, printed] // “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D0C3C6E2E4D43DEFA00FDBCB6E9" authority="Suffr." authorityName="Suffrian" authorityYear="1866" box="[428,603,1509,1535]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Metallactus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albivittis">albivittis Suffr.</taxonomicName>
* Allegr. Sellow.” [blue label, handwritten] // “Hist.-Coll. (
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D0C3C6E2E4D469EFA00FA8CB516" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[1260,1387,1509,1536]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
) Nr. 23960 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D0C3C6E2E4D4291F9ECFDF0B535" authority="Suffr." authorityName="Suffrian" authorityYear="1866" box="[227,535,1545,1571]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Metallactus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albivittis">Metallactus albivittis Suffr.</taxonomicName>
